---
hero:
  title: AI-Driven Enterprise Performance with Data You Can Trust
  subtitle: Free up cash, cut obsolete inventory, boost sales productivity, and unlock hidden capacity. With reliable data and AI that works with you, not against you, you’ll get the insights you need in minutes, instead of weeks.
  button_text: Schedule a discovery call
  button_target: https://meetings-eu1.hubspot.com/alessio-civitillo/book-a-call
  image: ./src/assets/images/backgrounds/sfondi-dyvenia08.jpg
intro:
  title: Companies collect more data than ever, but most can’t use it effectively.
  content: |-
    - **Slow insights:** By the time reports are ready, the opportunity has passed.
    - **Disconnected numbers:** Finance, sales, and operations waste hours reconciling mismatched data.
    - **Bad data = bad AI:** Without solid foundations and the right context, AI delivers inconsistent or misleading results.
    - **Fragmented systems:** ERPs, CRMs, and spreadsheets hold valuable data that rarely connect.
    - **Mounting pressure:** Finance and FP&A teams are expected to model scenarios and deliver answers in real time, but legacy tools can’t keep up.
highlight_one:
  title: Most enterprises are sitting on a goldmine of data, but struggle to use it effectively
  subtitle: |-
    - AI is racing ahead, but **95%** of manufacturing companies still **fail to implement it successfully**.
    - Only **3% of organizations meet basic data quality standards**.
    - Even though 82% of sales teams rack win rates, only **23% know what actually drives performance.**
highlight_two:
  title1: The Big Picture?
  title2: Unified, Good Quality Data that Drives Performance
  content: Too often, analytics initiatives fall short of their promises. Complex models built without a clear understanding of business can lead to confusing outputs rather than actionable insights. What businesses really need are simple, transparent data solutions that align teams and drive performance—solutions that provide clarity and deliver real results.
foundations_titles:
  title1: The 5 Key Attributes of
  title2: UNIFIED DATA
foundations_elements:
  - title: Comprehensive
    content: Detailed, structured data that captures all relevant dimensions for a complete view.
  - title: Trusted & Compliant
    content: Auditable, transparent data with clear lineage and no “black boxes.”
  - title: Aligned
    content: Consistent definitions and structures that ensure everyone in the organization works with the same data.
  - title: Stable & Adaptable
    content: Data that remains reliable and comparable, even through system changes, restatements, or organizational shifts.
  - title: Ready for Use
    content: Clean, consistent, and well-integrated data, prepared for analysis, AI-driven solutions, and decision-making.
about:
  title: Who we are
  content: |-
    We’re data and performance management experts who have worked inside the same finance, sales, and operations roles you lead today. We’ve seen how disconnected data and failed AI projects frustrate teams and slow down decisions. 

    We believe **AI is a competitive advantage only if it’s built on reliable data and clear business context**. That’s what we deliver.
whyus_intro:
  title: Addressing Your Struggles
  content: Business leaders lacking unified metrics suffer from one or more of these **12 challenges**
whyus_elements:
  - title: Slow Insights
    content: Waiting too long to access critical data delays decision-making and reduces agility.
  - title: Lack of Alignment
    content: Departments spend time and resources reconciling numbers that don't match, leading to wasted effort and confusion.
  - title: Trust Issues with Data
    content: Inconsistent, unreliable data erodes confidence and hinders informed decision-making.
  - title: Misused Talent
    content: Skilled analysts spend more time managing reports than driving strategic analysis.
  - title: Increasing Tech Debt
    content: Custom logic and complex dashboards create a fragmented system, understood by only a few, increasing long-term maintenance costs.
  - title: Disjointed Planning
    content: Lack of integrated data across departments leads to inefficiencies, missed targets, and outdated inventory.
  - title: Inconsistent Comparisons
    content: Frequent organizational changes and shifting data structures make it difficult to compare performance over time.
  - title: Poor Usability
    content: Hard-to-access, inconsistent data makes generating ad hoc reports and analyses slow and inefficient.
  - title: Data Silos
    content: Fragmented data across different departments or tools prevents a unified view of business performance, leading to missed opportunities.
  - title: Slow AI Adoption
    content: Without high-quality, well-structured data, AI and automation efforts struggle to deliver value.
  - title: Talent Retention Issues
    content: Frustration with outdated, inefficient data systems leads to disengagement and turnover.
  - title: Difficult Onboarding
    content: New analysts struggle to understand complex, fragmented data systems, delaying productivity.
our_services:
  title: Our Two-Step Approach to Integrated Data
  image: ./src/assets/images/backgrounds/sfondi-dyvenia26.jpg
our_services_items:
  - title: '& Strategy'
    prefix: Assessment
    description: We begin by analyzing your business strategy to identify gaps in your current data landscape. Through focused workshops and interviews with key business leaders, we define priorities and develop a clear data narrative that aligns with your objectives. From there, we create a detailed roadmap with resource planning to ensure a smooth transition to unified, high-quality data. To validate the approach, we deliver a Minimum Viable Product (MVP) that demonstrates tangible results.
  - title: '& Implementation'
    prefix: Execution
    description: For clients seeking end-to-end support, we assemble a dedicated team of data analysts, solution architects, and a project manager to execute the roadmap. This team ensures seamless integration, maintains clear communication across all levels, and collaborates closely with business leaders to align on goals. The result is a well-structured, reliable data foundation that drives performance and supports AI and digital transformation initiatives.
description: Driving Better Decisions and Business Performance with Unified Metrics
bodyClass: home
blog:
  title: Our Insights
  intro: Selected Articles. Check our blog for more.
layout: base
permalink: /index.html
title: dyvenia
---
<header class="section page-header">
  {% svg "divider/soft-top", null, "seperator" %}

  {% if hero.image %}
    {% image hero.image, "", null, "eager" %}
  {% endif %}

  <div class="section__inner region region-space-xl-2xl ">
    <div class="wrapper flow">
    <h1>{{ hero.title }}</h1>
      {{ hero.subtitle | markdownFormat | safe }}
      <a href="{{ hero.button_target }}" class="button flow-space-xl"> {{ hero.button_text }} {% svg "misc/arrow" %}</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<div class="intro | wrapper">
  <article class="region flow prose">
    <h2 class="text-step-2">{{ intro.title }}</h2>
    {{ intro.content | markdownFormat | safe }}
  </article>
</div>

<div class="highlight-one | wrapper">
  <div class="full wrapper section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-blue-accent)">
    <article class="full  intro | section__inner wrapper  region">
      <div class="feature flow prose">
        <h2 class="text-step-3">{{ highlight_one.title }} <span>*</span></h2>
        <p class="text-step-min-1"><span>*</span> {{ highlight_one.subtitle }}</p>
      </div>
      {% svg "brand/waves" %}
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="highlight-two | wrapper">
  <div class="full wrapper section" style="--spot-color: var(--color-blue-accent-6)">
    <article class="full  intro | section__inner wrapper region flow prose text-center text-blue-100">
      <h2 class="text-step-1">
        {{ highlight_two.title1 }}
        <span class="block text-step-3 text-blue-400 mt-2xs">{{ highlight_two.title2 }} </span>
      </h2>
      <p class="flow-space-l">{{ highlight_two.content }}</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="foundations | wrapper">
  <article class="full region flow">
    <h2 class="text-step-3 text-center">
      {{ foundations_titles.title1 }}
      <span class="block uppercase text-blue-500">{{ foundations_titles.title2 }} </span>
    </h2>
    <div class="split region">
      {% svg "brand/medusa-organic" %}
      <ol class="timeline">
        {% for key in foundations_elements %}
          <li>
            <span>{{ loop.index }}</span>
            <div class="flow flow-space-3xs">
              <h3 class="text-step-1">{{ key.title }}</h3>
              <p>{{ key.content }}</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        {% endfor %}
      </ol>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="about | wrapper">
  <article class="feature | region">
    <header class="grid" data-layout="thirds">
      <h2>{{ about.title }}</h2>
      <div class="flow">{{ about.content | markdownFormat | safe }}</div>
    </header>
    <div class="grid mt-xl-2xl" data-layout="thirds">
      {% for member in collections.team_members %}
      {% if member.data.show_on_about %}
        <div class="about__content flow">
          {% image "." + member.data.image, "" %}

          <h3>{{ member.data.name }}</h3>
          {{ member.data.description_short | markdownFormat | safe }}
        </div>
      {% endif %}
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="why | wrapper">
  <article class="feature | region flow">
    <header class="flow">
    <h2>{{ whyus_intro.title }}</h2>
      {{ whyus_intro.content | markdownFormat | safe }}
      </header>

      <dl class="flow region column" role="list">
        {% for key in whyus_elements %}
          <div class="flow">
            <dt class="font-bold text-purple">{{ key.title }}</dt>
            <dd>{{ key.content }}</dd>
          </div>
        {% endfor %}
      </dl>
  </article>
</div>

<div class="services | wrapper">

  {% if our_services.image %}
  {% image our_services.image, "" %}
  {% endif %}


    <article class="wrapper region flow">
        <h2 class="text-center">{{ our_services.title }}</h2>

          {% for item in our_services_items %}

            <div class="grid" data-layout="thirds">
              <h3>{{ item.prefix }} <span>{{ item.title }}</span></h3>
              <div>
              {{ item.description | markdownFormat | safe }}
            </div>
            </div>

          {% endfor %}
    </article>

</div>

<div class="wrapper">
  <section class="full | region">

    <div class="wrapper flow prose">
      <h2><a class="no-underline hover:underline" href="/insights/">{{ blog.title }}</a></h2>

      {% if blog.intro %}
        <p>{{ blog.intro }}</p>
      {% endif %}

      <div class="feature">
        <custom-masonry layout="50-50">

                   <!-- loop posts -->
         {% set itemList = collections.allPosts %}
         {% asyncEach item in itemList.slice(0, 4) %}
           {% set definedDate = item.date %}
           {% include "partials/card-blog.njk" %}
         {% endeach %}

        </custom-masonry>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>

{%- css "local" -%}
  {%- include "css/page-header.css" -%}
  {%- include 'css/home.css' -%}
  {%- include 'css/column.css' -%}
{%- endcss -%}
